1.title: Hamburger Paradise
1.plot: Fantastic food is more important to many travelers than museums, hotels and souvenirs, and in this episode, hamburgers are in the spotlight.

2.title: Pizza Paradise
2.plot: It's the well-rounded treat you just bake and eat. Fold it, stuff it, or eat it with a fork - any way you slice it, pizza is the ultimate Italian import.

3.title: Hot Dog Paradise
3.plot: The hot dog is the ultimate leisure food - fast, fun, and served in a bun. In Atlanta they like a southern slaw dog, in Chicago it's dragged through the garden, and in New Jersey they stuff their dogs in pizza bread. Hot Dog Paradise has them all.

4.title: Steak Paradise
4.plot: T-bone, porterhouse, New York strip, prime rib, filet mignon. So many cuts of steak, so little time. Come along as we explore the best of the best in the beef world, from the famous Peter Luger's in New York to the Big Texan Steak Ranch in Amarillo.

5.title: Deep Fried Paradise
5.plot: From Chicken to Steak, burgers to hot dogs and even the sides deep-fried pickles and Twinkies. They're frying it all up.

6.title: Donut Paradise
6.plot: From Crullers to Fritters and from Beignets to Bear Claws, the world of delicious deep fried dough is turned upside down in the search for Donut Paradise. Every glazed, jelly-filled, and chocolate covered creation is covered.

7.title: Barbecue Paradise
7.plot: Cooking meat over a fire is the American way, but throwing spaghetti on the grill? Barbecue Paradise takes the outdoor epicurean beyond backyard burgers to the most exquisite open flame eateries in the country.

8.title: Ice Cream Paradise
8.plot: Chocolate, strawberry, and vanilla are just the tip of the waffle cone as the hottest ice cold concoctions around the country are unearthed, including the oldest ice cream shop in America and the home of the very first ice cream cone.

9.title: Diner Paradise
9.plot: DINER PARADISE goes beyond the farmer's omelets, the chocolate shakes, and the meatloaf sandwiches to find the best places in the country to slide into a booth and order up a heaping helping of American history.

10.title: All You Can Eat Paradise
10.plot: America's yummiest, starring a dog covered in deep-fried cheese curds and gravy in Chicago, an alligator dog covered in guacamole and Andouille sauce in New Orleans, and a grilled dog topped with cream cheese in Seattle.

1.title: Minnesota State Fair
1.plot: Food Paradise travels to the Twin Cities and says 'you betcha' to the fabulous food found at the Minnesota State Fair. The annual event is a celebration of creative comfort food, like Meatloaf on a Stick and Beer Gelato.

2.title: Steak-Stravaganza
2.plot: America's most rare steaks, featuring a smoky center-cut sirloin in Malibu, a mouth-watering rib eye topped with spicy Chimichurri sauce in Miami, and a tender flank steak stuffed with gooey cheese and hard boiled eggs in Austin.

3.title: Weiner Takes All

4.title: Deli-Licious
4.plot: We're serving up deli dishes beyond your wildest cheat-day fantasies, from Reubens to brats to schnitzel sandwiches.

5.title: Hog Heaven
5.plot: It's a pork-a-palooza, starring a fall-off-the-bone whole hog covered in a tangy sauce in South Carolina, plump balls of pork shoulder doused with spicy mayo in Portland, and smoked pork wrapped in a net of thick bacon in Arizona.

2.title: Brunch-Nado
2.plot: What's better than breakfast or lunch? Well, brunch of course! It's the best of both worlds, and in this episode of Food Paradise, we bring to the table the best dishes and drinks from the most relaxed meal of the week.

3.title: Super Sandwiches
3.plot: We travel from coast to coast in search of the greatest eight places to find super sandwiches.

4.title: Pizza Party
4.plot: For pizza that goes beyond pepperoni, check out the Great 8 pizzerias from all over the country where they're slinging pies that defy expectations.

5.title: Southern Comfort Food
5.plot: You don't have to be from the South to enjoy down-home country cookin', you just have to be hungry! We leave no biscuit unturned in our search for the eight best Southern comfort food places this country has to offer.

6.title: Winner Winner Chicken Dinner
6.plot: From California to Virginia, we travel from state to state to find America's eight greatest chicken dishes.

7.title: Midnight Munchies
7.plot: Bar food has made great leaps forward in recent years, so Food Paradise stays up late to find 8 great places for midnight munchies.

9.title: Extra Cheesy
9.plot: On this episode of Food Paradise, we count down our 8 favorite places serving up the extra-cheesiest delights in the nation.

10.title: BBQ Bliss
10.plot: Food Paradise grills the usual suspects, and a few unusual ones, in hopes of smoking out 8 great places for BBQ bliss.

11.title: Iconic Eats
11.plot: Ever wonder where you can eat the best version of a city's signature dish? We're counting down the great eight restaurants serving up hometown heroes all over America

14.title: Vegas, Baby!
14.plot: Food Paradise heads to Las Vegas to uncover the best bites Sin City has to offer. From the swankiest steak house to the coolest poolside restaurant, we'll show you all the hottest hot spots on and off the strip.

15.title: Here's the Beef
15.plot: We're traveling coast-to-coast hitting the most sizzling hotspots for beef in the US from a high-end steakhouse in Manhattan to a rib joint in Oklahoma.

16.title: Feasting at the Fair
16.plot: We're traveling to the fairest of fairs in the nation, chowing down in the Land of Enchantment, sampling old favorites in New England and seeing what treats are whippin' across people's lips in Oklahoma!

17.title: Food with a View
17.plot: Food Paradise travels to restaurants that combine beautiful scenery with mouthwatering food. From the desert views of Sedona, Arizona, to the majestic beauty of the Teton Mountain range, get ready for a visual feast.

18.title: Passport on a Plate
18.plot: Food Paradise heads out on a global grub down adventure across the USA. From an authentic taste of Germany in Wisconsin to a Danish adventure in California, we travel the states for some delicious cultural cuisine.

19.title: Stuffed
19.plot: Road trip across America to discover the best stuffed foods in the nation. From a wrestling-themed restaurant in Chicago to a baked potato factory in Houston, there's nothing quite like these flavorful stuffed bites.

20.title: Taste of the Town
20.plot: Get a city's most famous food from the local hot spot that does it best. From wings in Buffalo, NY, to chili in Houston, Texas, find out which restaurants do their city's iconic dishes proud.

21.title: Sausage King
21.plot: Sausage works for breakfast, lunch, dinner -- and even a late-night snack. From Milwaukee-style brats in Wisconsin to fried chicken sausage in Texas, these are America's hot spots for one of its most universal foods

22.title: Pub Grub
22.plot: From San Francisco to Miami, FL, we're leaving no bar stool unturned as we tour restaurants around the country to see who's taking boring bar food and turning it into unique pub grub.

23.title: All American Classics
23.plot: A stateside hunt to find the best versions of classic American dishes. From hot dogs in Ohio to burgers in Oklahoma, these restaurants serve up nostalgic food with some innovative modern twists.

24.title: Stack Attack
24.plot: Food Paradise is on a Stack Attack from Atlanta to Los Angeles looking for the tallest meals in the country.

25.title: Like Mamma Made
25.plot: Local favorites feature comfort food just like mama used to make. From mac 'n' cheese in Detroit and chicken pot pie in Portland to fried chicken in Atlanta and meatloaf in Kansas City, these foods are warm, cozy and nostalgic.

26.title: Better with Bacon
26.plot: Restaurants across the country prove that everything is better with bacon, from bacon grenades in Chicago and bacon sushi in San Diego to bacon-wrapped wings in Vegas and an all-you-can-eat bacon buffet in Milwaukee.

imdb.title: Food Paradise
plot: Get a taste of America's one-of-a-kind dining experiences with the most mouth-watering and decadent specialties from around the country.
